<p>I have created an edittext which contains a list of words and images as shown below using the following function. However, if i include ~15 images in the edittext, it will lead to "out of memory error".</p>  <p>For loading a large group of images in ImageView, i am using Picasso or Universal ImageLoader and it is working fine. However, i don't know to apply it in editText.</p>  <pre><code>public static void insertImageIntoEditText(SpannableString ss,EditText editText){ Editable ed=editText.getText();  ed.insert(editText.getText().length(),"\n");  int start=Math.max(editText.getSelectionStart(),editText.getText().length()); editText.setSelection(start);  ed.insert(start, ss); ed.insert(start+ss.length(), "\n"); editText.setText(ed); editText.setSelection(start+ss.length()+1); }  public static void insertTextIntoEditText(String msg, EditText editText){ Editable ed=editText.getText();  int start=Math.max(editText.getSelectionStart(),             editText.getText().length());  ed.insert(start, msg); editText.setText(ed); } </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/UDmu1.jpg" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/UDmu1.jpg" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>